              <span id="reviewTextContainer3308367027" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14593906027123895724">Wow! I&apos;m really getting into this whole story! There was a lot of conflict in this volume and I found myself turning page after page, wanting more!<br/>What really got me excited about this volume was the inclusion of Green Plains and the Lima branch of the Church. In my own family history, I have family from this area and actually lived during this time period and persecution. My 8th great grandfather and his family left Green Plains to go to the refuge of Nauvoo when mobs started burning houses and</span>
  <span id="freeText14593906027123895724" style="display:none">Wow! I'm really getting into this whole story! There was a lot of conflict in this volume and I found myself turning page after page, wanting more!<br />What really got me excited about this volume was the inclusion of Green Plains and the Lima branch of the Church. In my own family history, I have family from this area and actually lived during this time period and persecution. My 8th great grandfather and his family left Green Plains to go to the refuge of Nauvoo when mobs started burning houses and property as described in the novel.<br />The ending was sooooo hard and filled me with all the sad emotions. It was so sad to see the end of Benjamin Steed's mortal journey, but at the same time, I was so happy the Steeds were able to get sealed in the Nauvoo temple.<br />This is such a bittersweet volume and I can't wait to follow the Steeds' journey across the plains and to the West.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14593906027123895724" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


